1
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:01,720
Today, you look brighter than usual.

2
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:04,040
It seems like...

3
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:06,200
you’ve come up with a new story again, haven’t you?

4
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,760
Not exactly a new story.

5
00:01:09,858 --> 00:01:10,980
Maybe...

6
00:01:11,019 --> 00:01:12,961
it’s a sequel to the old one.

7
00:01:13,956 --> 00:01:15,100
One I’ve only just begun to understand.

8
00:01:16,484 --> 00:01:18,060
That sounds interesting.

9
00:01:19,260 --> 00:01:20,500
What’s it called?

10
00:01:22,077 --> 00:01:25,040
No Rule After I Fell for You.

11
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:31,480
Is that so?

12
00:01:32,941 --> 00:01:35,740
Sounds like someone became your inspiration.

13
00:01:36,964 --> 00:01:38,060
Maybe.

14
00:01:39,142 --> 00:01:40,782
But this time...

15
00:01:41,034 --> 00:01:43,034
I think I’ll write from real feelings.

16
00:01:43,918 --> 00:01:45,256
Not from theories.

17
00:01:46,377 --> 00:01:47,220
That’s the problem...

18
00:01:47,589 --> 00:01:50,040
with people who try to understand everything.

19
00:01:50,450 --> 00:01:51,620
The harder you try not to feel...

20
00:01:52,176 --> 00:01:53,300
the deeper you drown in it.

21
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,340
But sometimes...

22
00:01:55,581 --> 00:01:56,600
understanding something...

23
00:01:57,109 --> 00:01:58,760
can make it hurt less.

24
00:01:59,633 --> 00:02:02,020
But it might also make you remember it longer.

25
00:02:07,951 --> 00:02:10,880
I have to go back to Bangkok tomorrow.

26
00:02:14,506 --> 00:02:15,006
I see.

27
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,440
I need to sort some things out with myself.

28
00:02:22,568 --> 00:02:23,860
That sounds...

29
00:02:24,001 --> 00:02:26,300
harder than writing an entire book.

30
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,494
It is.

31
00:02:29,358 --> 00:02:31,486
Because this time...

32
00:02:32,154 --> 00:02:33,306
there’s no script to revise.

33
00:02:33,799 --> 00:02:34,500
And...

34
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:36,619
no character to hide behind.

35
00:02:39,504 --> 00:02:41,087
As long as you have a heart...

36
00:02:41,746 --> 00:02:42,724
that’s enough.

37
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:01,120
We’re always afraid of the ending of a relationship.

38
00:03:01,583 --> 00:03:03,000
When really...

39
00:03:03,544 --> 00:03:06,000
it might just be the beginning of missing someone.

40
00:03:07,191 --> 00:03:08,843
Because real feelings...

41
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:10,856
don’t disappear with time.

42
00:03:11,427 --> 00:03:14,844
They simply turn into longing.

43
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:38,640
You’re up early.

44
00:03:39,411 --> 00:03:41,202
I came to send off a writer.

45
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:43,060
I was afraid she’d leave without saying goodbye.

46
00:03:44,646 --> 00:03:46,414
I won’t run away.

47
00:03:46,804 --> 00:03:50,283
I just have to go back and start writing a new chapter.

48
00:03:52,828 --> 00:03:54,408
Can I ask you something?

49
00:03:56,074 --> 00:03:56,574
Of course.

50
00:03:58,023 --> 00:03:59,431
Your new book...

51
00:04:00,048 --> 00:04:01,456
will you write about me?

52
00:04:04,066 --> 00:04:05,680
Maybe I won’t have to.

53
00:04:07,318 --> 00:04:10,180
If you’re already living in my heart.

54
00:04:12,220 --> 00:04:13,320
I’ll wait to read it.

55
00:04:13,726 --> 00:04:16,720
Even if my name isn’t in the book.

56
00:04:19,566 --> 00:04:20,600
Maybe...

57
00:04:21,283 --> 00:04:24,440
you’ll be on every page without even knowing it.

58
00:04:45,066 --> 00:04:46,400
I once wrote...

59
00:04:46,866 --> 00:04:49,300
if you still want to see someone’s face the next morning...

60
00:04:49,454 --> 00:04:51,222
it means you’re truly starting to like them.

61
00:04:51,844 --> 00:04:52,717
But today...

62
00:04:52,861 --> 00:04:54,489
I don’t want to prove it anymore.

63
00:04:54,988 --> 00:04:56,698
I just want...

64
00:04:56,886 --> 00:04:58,294
them to still be there...

65
00:04:59,264 --> 00:05:01,996
when tomorrow comes.

66
00:05:02,472 --> 00:05:05,240
Every theory exists to search for the truth.

67
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,000
But sometimes, the truth of the heart...

68
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
doesn’t need any theory at all.

69
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,960
I started writing this book...

70
00:05:30,343 --> 00:05:32,343
because I wanted to prove the theory of love.

71
00:05:32,953 --> 00:05:34,779
But by the final chapter...

72
00:05:35,107 --> 00:05:36,677
I finally understood...

73
00:05:37,129 --> 00:05:39,129
love never needed a reason.

74
00:05:39,894 --> 00:05:40,701
It only needed someone...

75
00:05:40,701 --> 00:05:42,003
to stay beside us...

76
00:05:42,003 --> 00:05:43,811
while we were learning how to understand it.

77
00:05:44,489 --> 00:05:45,633
We may not understand...

78
00:05:45,633 --> 00:05:47,281
every equation in this world.

79
00:05:47,841 --> 00:05:49,099
But we know...

80
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:50,870
some people don’t come into our lives...

81
00:05:50,870 --> 00:05:52,866
to be understood.

82
00:05:53,279 --> 00:05:54,868
They simply come...

83
00:05:54,868 --> 00:05:57,000
to turn our theories...

84
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:01,291
into something real.

85
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,820
Tyme, seriously...

86
00:06:12,001 --> 00:06:14,700
How many times have you reread my book?

87
00:06:16,914 --> 00:06:18,040
Probably eight times already.

88
00:06:18,992 --> 00:06:20,028
Eight times?

89
00:06:20,590 --> 00:06:21,521
Don’t you get bored?

90
00:06:22,402 --> 00:06:24,900
Well, you still haven’t finished your new book.

91
00:06:24,991 --> 00:06:26,432
What else am I supposed to do?

92
00:06:27,661 --> 00:06:30,073
So I just keep rereading the old one.

93
00:06:32,056 --> 00:06:33,417
I finished writing it.

94
00:06:33,658 --> 00:06:34,158
Hey!

95
00:06:35,721 --> 00:06:36,600
Really?

96
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,918
Let me read it!

97
00:06:38,757 --> 00:06:39,282
No way.

98
00:06:40,835 --> 00:06:42,160
Why not?

99
00:06:42,482 --> 00:06:43,320
Or...

100
00:06:43,715 --> 00:06:45,436
are you afraid I’ll realize...

101
00:06:45,677 --> 00:06:46,690
the whole story is about me?

102
00:06:47,643 --> 00:06:48,540
Well...

103
00:06:50,426 --> 00:06:50,909
Wait...

104
00:06:50,909 --> 00:06:53,260
So you really did write about us?

105
00:06:55,937 --> 00:06:58,860
You’re only saying that because you want credit, right?

106
00:06:59,977 --> 00:07:00,760
Of course.

107
00:07:01,149 --> 00:07:04,175
At the very least, my name should appear under inspiration.

108
00:07:05,151 --> 00:07:06,899
Inspiration?

109
00:07:07,381 --> 00:07:08,347
I think...

110
00:07:08,770 --> 00:07:11,374
your name belongs under the warning label instead.

111
00:07:13,764 --> 00:07:14,564
I don’t care.

112
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:16,480
I’m still going to...

113
00:07:16,962 --> 00:07:17,742
keep reading...

114
00:07:18,350 --> 00:07:20,350
the old book over and over again.

115
00:07:27,213 --> 00:07:28,300
Stop reading already.

116
00:07:30,458 --> 00:07:31,808
Seriously, stop reading.

117
00:07:37,166 --> 00:07:38,360
You still won’t stop?

118
00:07:43,484 --> 00:07:45,270
So you’re really not going to stop reading, huh?

119
00:08:28,278 --> 00:08:30,646
A true story that began with theory...

120
00:08:30,782 --> 00:08:32,782
and ended with the heart.
